Package sttrswing.model.validator

Class WarpCoordValidator

Object
Validator
WarpCoordValidator
public class WarpCoordValidator extends Validator
Validator responsible for validating if the user String input can be evaluated as * conforming to either a NUMBER,NUMBER or NUMBER,NUMBER.NUMBER pattern.

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid(String input)
      Takes the given String input and return if the given String input can be evaluated as conforming to either a DIGIT,DIGIT or DIGIT,DIGIT.DIGIT pattern. Examples of valid inputs:
      • 1, 1
      • 5, 0.1
      • 2, 0.4
      Examples of invalid inputs:
      • 10,0
      • -1,0
      • 1,
      • 5,0.1
      • 0.5,1
      Overrides:
      isValid in class Validator
      Parameters:
      input - - The given String we wish to evaluate.
      Returns:
      if the given String input can be evaluated as conforming to either a DIGIT,DIGIT or DIGIT,DIGIT.DIGIT pattern.
